<h2 id="question-1">Question 1</h2>
<p>Cat, head and tail commands are used for displaying the content of a file.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Display the content of the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/etc/passwd</code> file.</li>
  <li>Display the content of the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/etc/passwd</code> file in reverse order.</li>
  <li>Display the content of the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/etc/passwd</code> file with line numbers and the $ to indicate the end of every line.</li>
  <li>Display the first 5 lines of a the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/etc/passwd</code> file.</li>
  <li>Display the last 5 lines of the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/etc/passwd</code> file.</li>
</ol>

